# NOVAT is the only product

## Product lineage (memorize this)
- **NOVAT** = the product formerly called **Mooncrew** (same app, rebranded).
- **Nova** / **Life OS** = **dead** as product names. Do not ship, brand, or treat them as the product.
- Do **not** confuse **Nova** with **NOVAT** — they are not the same thing.

## User-facing name
- Always **NOVAT** in UI, titles, EXE, docs headlines, PWA name.
- Internal code paths may still say `flowdo`, `workorganizer`, `mooncrew` (compat), `novaApi` — fine.
- Never user-facing: Nova, NOVA, Life OS, LifeOS, Mooncrew (as current brand), Flowdo (as product name).

## Shipping target (default always)
- **Repo:** `C:\Users\Anwender\flowdo-review`
- **GitHub:** `nelkejannis-lab/flowdo`
- **Production:** https://novat.app
- Implement features, fixes, deploys, EXE builds, and releases **here** unless the user explicitly names another repo.

## Always ship live immediately
- When a feature/fix is done: **commit → push → deploy novat.app in the same pass**. Do not leave finished work only on disk.
- Prefer also publishing the NOVAT EXE GitHub release on version bumps.
- Fresh Vercel build every time (pull → repair `[SENSITIVE]` placeholders → `vercel build --prod` → deploy). Never stale prebuilt alone.
- User said: „mache alles live immer direkt“ / „push everything live“.

## life-os / "Nova" repos
- Do **not** implement in `life-os` / `life-os-review` unless the user **explicitly** asks.
- Work done there must be **ported into NOVAT** or ignored going forward — never continue shipping Nova/Life OS.

